wiki.content: "Whiplash" is a song recorded by the South Korean girl group aespa. It was released on October 21st, 2024, as the title track of their fifth mini album, 'Whiplash', under SM Entertainment. Whiplash is an EDM-based dance song featuring a strong, intense, and fast-paced bass and house beats. The lyrics contain the confident charm of aespa, who boldly advances without being confined by a mold and changes the landscape wherever they go, and the members’ cool and unique vocals add to the fun of listening to the minimal track and addictive top line. Described as a dance song featuring an intense and fast-paced bass and house beat, the Iyrics contain the charm of aespa, who are unconventional and move forward with their own standards without hesitation. The minimalist track and addictive topline are presented with the members' cool and unique vocals to make it more fun to listen to. "Whiplash" was written by Leslie of XYXX, while the composition, arrangement and music production were handled by Lewis Jankel and Neil Ormandy, with Marcus "MarcLo" Lomax, Neil Ormandy, Rosina "Soaky Siren" Russell, and Lewis Jankel participating in the composition.
